1
00:00:01,240 --> 00:00:09,570

2
00:00:13,390 --> 00:00:15,899

3
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:18,650

4
00:00:18,650 --> 00:00:21,380

5
00:00:21,380 --> 00:00:23,980

6
00:00:32,229 --> 00:00:35,120

7
00:00:45,540 --> 00:00:48,210
You won't remember a thing.

8
00:00:49,130 --> 00:00:51,850
When you wake up,

9
00:00:51,850 --> 00:00:54,470
everything will be over.

10
00:01:04,180 --> 00:01:07,230
You just had a short dream, Miss Dam.

11
00:01:10,120 --> 00:01:11,810
As of now,

12
00:01:13,250 --> 00:01:15,130
our contract is over.

13
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:04,229
 Noona, come on out. Breakfast is ready.

14
00:02:04,230 --> 00:02:06,070
Okay.

15
00:02:09,729 --> 00:02:12,499
- Hey, you need to get up. 
 - Come on.

16
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:16,020
Are you a human or a slug?

17
00:02:16,020 --> 00:02:18,659
Hey, what's for breakfast?

18
00:02:18,660 --> 00:02:21,800
- Chicken porridge. 
 - Nice.

19
00:02:24,170 --> 00:02:26,270
Chicken porridge.

20
00:02:29,530 --> 00:02:31,899
I'm leaving. Wash the dishes before you go.

21
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:33,690
Okay.

22
00:02:33,690 --> 00:02:35,119
Or at least leave them to soak.

23
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:38,840
Okay, you're nagging me so much!

24
00:02:42,160 --> 00:02:44,490
This is good.

25
00:02:46,560 --> 00:02:48,590

26
00:02:48,590 --> 00:02:49,859
Dam!

27
00:02:49,860 --> 00:02:52,820
- Hi. 
 - Hi. Doing okay?

28
00:02:52,820 --> 00:02:54,649
- Going to the Cultural Studies lecture? 
 - Yes.

29
00:02:54,650 --> 00:02:57,080
Going to the first period right after midterms is tough.

30
00:02:57,080 --> 00:02:58,659
I'm so tired.

31
00:02:58,660 --> 00:03:00,820
Right, have you heard?

32
00:03:00,820 --> 00:03:03,720
- Hear what? 
 - Listen.

33
00:03:06,630 --> 00:03:09,169
The Engineering Department cafeteria just added carbonara to the menu.

34
00:03:09,170 --> 00:03:12,289
- Yes! 
 - Wow, hey.

35
00:03:12,290 --> 00:03:14,669
We can't pass on a new menu item.

36
00:03:14,670 --> 00:03:17,219
- Lunch is at Engineering today! 
 - Of course.

37
00:03:17,220 --> 00:03:19,949
Whoever gets there first orders for everyone.

38
00:03:19,950 --> 00:03:20,959
- Okay. 
 - Okay.

39
00:03:20,960 --> 00:03:22,660
- Bye. 
 - Bye.

40
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:25,270
Hey, wait up!

41
00:03:27,120 --> 00:03:29,409
So I'll eat lunch with those two.

42
00:03:29,410 --> 00:03:32,619
Then I have a team project meeting for my major.

43
00:03:32,620 --> 00:03:35,670
In the afternoon, work on the group assignment.

44
00:03:35,670 --> 00:03:37,350
And...

45
00:03:38,650 --> 00:03:40,380
And...

46
00:04:01,530 --> 00:04:03,020
Shoot.

47
00:04:04,110 --> 00:04:06,910
The least he can do is make me forget everything.

48
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,220
Lee Dam?

49
00:04:33,220 --> 00:04:35,690
What are you doing here—

50
00:04:35,690 --> 00:04:37,650
Hey, are you crying?

51
00:04:39,430 --> 00:04:41,749
What's wrong? Is something going on?

52
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,870
Are you sick?

53
00:04:43,870 --> 00:04:47,150
Just go, please.

54
00:04:48,310 --> 00:04:51,360
How can I leave you here when you're like this?

55
00:04:54,820 --> 00:04:57,420
Let's sit on the bench, okay?

56
00:04:57,420 --> 00:04:59,180
You should at least sit and cry.

57
00:04:59,180 --> 00:05:01,200
Get up. I'll take your bag.

58
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:04,040
Okay. Get up.

59
00:05:37,590 --> 00:05:39,180
Hye Sun.

60
00:05:39,880 --> 00:05:42,620
You know we have to go on one more date

61
00:05:42,620 --> 00:05:44,489
for the project, right?

62
00:05:44,490 --> 00:05:48,380
Really? We still have another one?

63
00:05:49,340 --> 00:05:53,030
Yes, sadly, we have one more.

64
00:05:54,850 --> 00:05:57,469
If you're free on Saturday, want to go on a date?

65
00:05:57,470 --> 00:05:59,430
Whatever.

66
00:06:01,790 --> 00:06:03,600
If it's annoying,

67
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:06,880
do you just want to say we did and make up the report?

68
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:08,690
Can we do that?

69
00:06:08,690 --> 00:06:13,540
Yes, if we just get our stories straight, from mouth to mouth...

70
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:15,920
We have to... mouth to mouth?

71
00:06:15,920 --> 00:06:18,960
Yes, kind of.

72
00:06:18,960 --> 00:06:22,189
Wait, why do we have to mouth to mouth over some assignment?

73
00:06:22,190 --> 00:06:23,649
Well,

74
00:06:23,650 --> 00:06:27,079
we need to do well to get a good grade,

75
00:06:27,080 --> 00:06:28,529
so that it's easier to find a job—

76
00:06:28,530 --> 00:06:31,540
It'll even affect our job search?

77
00:06:37,470 --> 00:06:42,620
All right. I heard employment is the top priority for young people these days.

78
00:06:42,620 --> 00:06:45,440
If it's that important,

79
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:47,540
then fine. Let's do it!

80
00:06:48,520 --> 00:06:50,060
What?

81
00:06:57,220 --> 00:06:59,790
Hey, what are you doing? Are you crazy? Let go!

82
00:06:59,790 --> 00:07:01,439
Let me go. What's with you?

83
00:07:01,440 --> 00:07:03,730
- No, hey. 
 - Let me go.

84
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:05,870

85
00:07:05,870 --> 00:07:08,439
What are you doing? Have you gone insane?

86
00:07:08,440 --> 00:07:12,409
How can you strangle my swan-like throat like you're killing a chicken?

87
00:07:12,409 --> 00:07:14,390
Why did you...

88
00:07:16,890 --> 00:07:21,560
 Right, she's not good at Korean because she lived abroad.

89
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:25,340
Hye Sun, listen.

90
00:07:27,060 --> 00:07:29,779
There is this thing called "a figure of speech".

91
00:07:29,780 --> 00:07:31,790
So when we say "take off our shoes and step forward,"

92
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:33,739
it doesn't mean we really take off our shoes.

93
00:07:33,740 --> 00:07:36,419
It means we should do everything we can to help.

94
00:07:36,420 --> 00:07:39,459
And to "mouth to mouth" means

95
00:07:39,460 --> 00:07:41,259
to agree on a story ahead of time,

96
00:07:41,260 --> 00:07:44,880
so that the stories coming out of our mouths match when we make things up.

97
00:07:48,009 --> 00:07:50,340
Do you think you can teach me something?

98
00:07:50,340 --> 00:07:51,908
- No. 
 - I'm not uneducated.

99
00:07:51,909 --> 00:07:53,940
I even mastered the Thousand Character Classic! 
  (T/N: A poem used as a primer to teach Chinese characters to children since ancient times.)

100
00:07:53,940 --> 00:07:58,070
I may not have finished Lesser Learning, but I got into college! 
 (T/N: an ancient introductory education textbook.)

101
00:07:58,070 --> 00:08:00,950
Do you think I didn't even know that?

102
00:08:00,950 --> 00:08:05,619
 Wait, she thinks Lesser Learning is related to going to college?

103
00:08:08,770 --> 00:08:11,640
 She's a pretty funny girl.

104
00:08:11,640 --> 00:08:14,169
I'll see you on Saturday. Instead of "mouth to mouth"—

105
00:08:14,170 --> 00:08:17,379
I mean, instead of coming up with a story,

106
00:08:17,380 --> 00:08:19,099
let's just meet up.

107
00:08:19,100 --> 00:08:21,919
I get it. Go away.

108
00:08:21,920 --> 00:08:24,400
All right. See you on Saturday.

109
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:39,260
 She's not the type to tell me why she's crying, even if I ask.

110
00:08:45,190 --> 00:08:49,740
 How can I still be happy to see her in this situation?

111
00:09:00,220 --> 00:09:02,630
What's this?

112
00:09:02,630 --> 00:09:05,670
Why is she crying next to that Tiger Boy?

113
00:09:13,450 --> 00:09:15,480
It can't be!

114
00:09:38,540 --> 00:09:41,029
Please excuse me. You should get to class too.

115
00:09:41,030 --> 00:09:44,920
Hey, wait. Do you want to meet this weekend?

116
00:09:47,450 --> 00:09:50,540
No, that's not what I meant.

117
00:09:50,540 --> 00:09:54,490
I mean, well, it is.

118
00:09:54,490 --> 00:09:58,180
Let's do the couple assignment together. You don't want to?

119
00:09:59,770 --> 00:10:01,090
I don't want to.

120
00:10:50,410 --> 00:10:53,160
 Sir, I'm home!

121
00:10:58,330 --> 00:11:00,680
Why didn't you pick up your phone?

122
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:08,600
You took the Bead out, didn't you?

123
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,609
I could tell from how she looked.

124
00:11:10,610 --> 00:11:11,749
You saw Miss Dam?

125
00:11:11,750 --> 00:11:13,339
So what if I did?

126
00:11:13,340 --> 00:11:17,540
Why do you care? You won't be seeing her again.

127
00:11:17,540 --> 00:11:19,009
If you decided to drain every drop of energy

128
00:11:19,010 --> 00:11:21,240
from a stranger then abandon her,

129
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:23,270
you shouldn't have gotten attached.

130
00:11:23,270 --> 00:11:24,639
And if you've let her go,

131
00:11:24,640 --> 00:11:27,500
you need to move on and find the next target.

132
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:30,279
You don't have time to waste on wallowing,

133
00:11:30,280 --> 00:11:32,410
and that goes for both of you.

134
00:11:32,410 --> 00:11:34,420
Both of us?

135
00:11:34,420 --> 00:11:36,169
She was crying.

136
00:11:36,170 --> 00:11:38,460
She was? Why?

137
00:11:38,460 --> 00:11:39,599
Why are you asking me?

138
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:42,700
It must be because of you.

139
00:11:42,700 --> 00:11:44,700
That's impossible.

140
00:11:44,700 --> 00:11:47,940
I erased everything about me from her memories.

141
00:11:47,940 --> 00:11:51,650
I don't know if that's kind or cruel.

142
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:55,969
Are you sure your magic worked?

143
00:11:55,970 --> 00:11:58,389
You said it didn't work on her mom.

144
00:11:58,390 --> 00:12:01,250
No one will remember a thing.

145
00:12:01,820 --> 00:12:04,020
Not her,

146
00:12:04,020 --> 00:12:06,330
and not anyone else who saw me.

147
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:10,619
Please look after her, make sure she's doing well

148
00:12:10,620 --> 00:12:12,700
and stays healthy.

149
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:15,599
You said you wanted me to keep her safe,

150
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:18,180
not pry into her private life.

151
00:12:18,180 --> 00:12:20,000
She's safe now.

152
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:22,070
From whom?

153
00:12:22,070 --> 00:12:23,850
From me.

154
00:12:26,380 --> 00:12:30,550
So now you're worried about her private life

155
00:12:31,070 --> 00:12:34,210
instead of her safety?

156
00:12:43,230 --> 00:12:46,140
I used to think of her as family.

157
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:48,160
Do me this favor.

158
00:12:49,070 --> 00:12:52,190
No. If you miss her, go see her yourself.

159
00:12:52,950 --> 00:12:56,840
She won't recognize you anyway, so what's the problem?

160
00:13:06,840 --> 00:13:08,650
Family, my foot.

161
00:13:08,650 --> 00:13:13,030
No guy looks like that over a girl he considers family.

162
00:13:14,420 --> 00:13:16,820
 Why, how do I look?

163
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:19,800
How can I put this?

164
00:13:20,930 --> 00:13:23,179
I mean, you've been smiling,

165
00:13:23,180 --> 00:13:25,159
but you look like you're empty inside.

166
00:13:25,160 --> 00:13:26,760
What are you saying?

167
00:13:26,760 --> 00:13:28,780
Are you sure nothing is going on?

168
00:13:28,780 --> 00:13:31,040
- I'm fine. 
 - Okay.

169
00:13:57,850 --> 00:14:00,230
 I lied.

170
00:14:00,750 --> 00:14:02,950
 I knew how to take out the Bead

171
00:14:02,950 --> 00:14:05,780
 from the beginning.

172
00:14:07,220 --> 00:14:10,070
 But I lied to you.

173
00:14:11,490 --> 00:14:16,060
 I needed energy to become human,

174
00:14:16,810 --> 00:14:19,550
 and you, of all people, had to be there.

175
00:14:21,430 --> 00:14:24,249
 Yes, I was just a consumable

176
00:14:24,250 --> 00:14:28,490
 to be used for my energy and cast aside.

177
00:14:28,490 --> 00:14:30,810
 So let's end it here.

178
00:14:30,810 --> 00:14:34,700
 Why am I crying when I should be celebrating?

179
00:14:35,340 --> 00:14:37,179
Soo Kyeong, are you free today?

180
00:14:37,180 --> 00:14:38,589
Today?

181
00:14:38,590 --> 00:14:41,539
I don't have to go to the academy.

182
00:14:41,540 --> 00:14:44,799
And my phone English lesson isn't today either.

183
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:47,079
Then let's call Jae Jin and party all night.

184
00:14:47,080 --> 00:14:48,770
Midterms are over too.

185
00:14:48,770 --> 00:14:53,160
I'm going to do everything I couldn't do for a while.

186
00:15:26,110 --> 00:15:27,940
That's the stuff!

187
00:15:27,940 --> 00:15:31,840
Chicken and beer beat any kind of relationship.

188
00:15:31,840 --> 00:15:34,339
I feel tipsy and satisfied,

189
00:15:34,340 --> 00:15:37,199
satisfied and tipsy!

190
00:15:37,200 --> 00:15:39,460
- I missed this so much. 
 - Well,

191
00:15:39,460 --> 00:15:41,249
did you have time to miss it?

192
00:15:41,250 --> 00:15:43,359
You do this practically every other night.

193
00:15:43,360 --> 00:15:46,609
Tell me about it. You'd think she hasn't done this for months!

194
00:15:46,610 --> 00:15:49,240
Excuse me, we'll take another garlic chicken

195
00:15:49,240 --> 00:15:51,009
and another pitcher of beer.

196
00:15:51,010 --> 00:15:52,819
 - Sure.  
 - You're eating more?

197
00:15:52,820 --> 00:15:55,390
Do you plan to stop eating chicken after today?

198
00:15:55,390 --> 00:15:57,089
I know midterms are over,

199
00:15:57,090 --> 00:16:00,000
but we should review today's lecture and study for tomorrow!

200
00:16:00,610 --> 00:16:02,880
Let's stop eating and get going.

201
00:16:02,880 --> 00:16:04,470
Hey, go where?

202
00:16:04,470 --> 00:16:07,119
My curfew's finally lifted. We have to stay out!

203
00:16:07,120 --> 00:16:08,710
You had a curfew?

204
00:16:08,710 --> 00:16:12,490
- I didn't know Dan was so strict. 
 - Right?

205
00:16:17,530 --> 00:16:19,309
I don't have to avoid them anymore.

206
00:16:19,310 --> 00:16:21,050
- What? 
 - What?

207
00:16:22,390 --> 00:16:24,589
My life is filled with happiness,

208
00:16:24,590 --> 00:16:25,810
I feel so free!

209
00:16:25,810 --> 00:16:28,300
Hey, let's go to noraebang!

210
00:16:28,300 --> 00:16:29,999
Noraebang sounds great.

211
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:33,830
Is it time for Jae Jin's trademark emotional ballads?

212
00:16:37,570 --> 00:16:38,929
Hey.

213
00:16:38,930 --> 00:16:41,789
I don't mean those drowsy slow songs.

214
00:16:41,790 --> 00:16:44,220
Let's go with dance music. Dance!

215
00:16:44,220 --> 00:16:46,790
Dance, dance!

216
00:17:41,410 --> 00:17:44,269
Why is Dam so hyper today? She's scaring me.

217
00:17:44,270 --> 00:17:45,810
I'm not sure.

218
00:17:45,810 --> 00:17:48,400
She kept saying that she feels free.

219
00:17:48,400 --> 00:17:49,769
Is it because exams are over?

220
00:17:49,770 --> 00:17:51,770
I don't think she studied so hard

221
00:17:51,770 --> 00:17:55,020
that she would feel this free.

222
00:17:59,320 --> 00:18:00,930
We have a minute left. Let's go.

223
00:18:00,930 --> 00:18:03,700
Let's not sing a long song to stretch it out,

224
00:18:03,700 --> 00:18:06,750
- and leave with some class. 
 - Start.

225
00:18:08,130 --> 00:18:09,030

226
00:18:10,680 --> 00:18:13,760
What's with this song, Dam? Did your taste change?

227
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:17,810
Well, I guess trot music is big these days.

228
